tool_description: Customize the Asana experience, leverage your data with the Asana.
name: Asana
title: Asana

api_list.name: addCommentToTask
api_list.description: Adds a comment to a task. The comment will be authored by the currently authenticated user, and timestamped when the server receives the request.

required_parameters.name: task
required_parameters.description: Globally unique identifier for the task.

required_parameters.name: text
required_parameters.description: The plain text of the comment to add.

api_list.name: addFollowersToTask
api_list.description: Adds each of the specified followers to the task, if they are not already following. Returns the complete, updated record for the affected task.

required_parameters.name: task
required_parameters.description: The task to add followers to.

required_parameters.name: followers
required_parameters.description: List of followers to add to the task.

api_list.name: addTagToTask
api_list.description: Adds a tag to a task. Returns an empty data block.

required_parameters.name: tag
required_parameters.description: The tag to add to the task.

required_parameters.name: task
required_parameters.description: The task to add a tag to.

api_list.name: addTaskToProject
api_list.description: Adds the task to the specified project, in the optional location specified. If no location arguments are given, the task will be added to the end of the project.

required_parameters.name: project
required_parameters.description: The project to add the task to.

required_parameters.name: task
required_parameters.description: The task to add to a project.

optional_parameters.name: insertBefore
optional_parameters.description: A task in the project to insert the task before, or null to insert at the end of the list.

optional_parameters.name: insertAfter
optional_parameters.description: A task in the project to insert the task after, or null to insert at the beginning of the list.

optional_parameters.name: section
optional_parameters.description: A section in the project to insert the task into. The task will be inserted at the bottom of the section.

api_list.name: addUserToTeam
api_list.description: The user making this call must be a member of the team in order to add others.

required_parameters.name: team
required_parameters.description: Globally unique identifier for the team.

required_parameters.name: user
required_parameters.description: An identifier for the user. Can be one of an email address, the globally unique identifier for the user, or the keyword me to indicate the current user making the request.

api_list.name: addUserToWorkspace
api_list.description: The user can be referenced by their globally unique user ID or their email address. Returns the full user record for the invited user.

required_parameters.name: user
required_parameters.description: An identifier for the user. Can be one of an email address, the globally unique identifier for the user, or the keyword me to indicate the current user making the request.

required_parameters.name: workspace
required_parameters.description: The workspace or organization to invite the user to.

api_list.name: createProject
api_list.description: Creates a new project in a workspace or team.

required_parameters.name: team
required_parameters.description: If creating in an organization, the specific team to create the project in.

required_parameters.name: workspace
required_parameters.description: The workspace or organization to create the project in.

optional_parameters.name: notes
optional_parameters.description: Project notes

api_list.name: createProjectCustomFieldSetting
api_list.description: Create a new custom field setting on the project.

required_parameters.name: project
required_parameters.description: The project to associate the custom field with.

required_parameters.name: customField
required_parameters.description: The id of the custom field to associate with this project.

optional_parameters.name: insertAfter
optional_parameters.description: An id of a Custom Field Settings on this project, after which the new Custom Field Settings will be added. insert_before and insert_after parameters cannot both be specified.

optional_parameters.name: isImportant
optional_parameters.description: Whether this field should be considered important to this project.

optional_parameters.name: insertBefore
optional_parameters.description: An id of a Custom Field Settings on this project, before which the new Custom Field Settings will be added. insert_before and insert_after parameters cannot both be specified.

api_list.name: createSection
api_list.description: Creates a new section in a project.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: The text to be displayed as the section name. This cannot be an empty string..

required_parameters.name: project
required_parameters.description: The project to associate the custom field with.

api_list.name: createSubtask
api_list.description: Creates a new subtask and adds it to the parent task. Returns the full record for the newly created subtask.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: Name of the task. This is generally a short sentence fragment that fits on a line in the UI for maximum readability. However, it can be longer.

required_parameters.name: task
required_parameters.description: The task to add a subtask to.

optional_parameters.name: notes
optional_parameters.description: More detailed, free-form textual information associated with the task.

optional_parameters.name: assignee
optional_parameters.description: User to which this task is assigned, or null if the task is unassigned.

optional_parameters.name: followers
optional_parameters.description: List of users following this task.

api_list.name: createTag
api_list.description: Creates a new tag in a workspace or organization.

required_parameters.name: workspace
required_parameters.description: The workspace or organization to create the tag in.

api_list.name: createTask
api_list.description: Creating a new task.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: Name of the task. This is generally a short sentence fragment that fits on a line in the UI for maximum readability. However, it can be longer.

required_parameters.name: workspace
required_parameters.description: The workspace to create a task in.

optional_parameters.name: notes
optional_parameters.description: More detailed, free-form textual information associated with the task.

optional_parameters.name: assignee
optional_parameters.description: User to which this task is assigned, or null if the task is unassigned.

optional_parameters.name: followers

api_list.name: createWebhook
api_list.description: Establishing a webhook is a two-part process. First, a simple HTTP POST similar to any other resource creation. Since you could have multiple webhooks we recommend specifying a unique local id for each target.

required_parameters.name: resource
required_parameters.description: A resource ID to subscribe to. The resource can be a task or project.

required_parameters.name: target
required_parameters.description: The URL to receive the HTTP POST.

api_list.name: deleteProject
api_list.description: A specific, existing project can be deleted by making a DELETE request on the URL for that project.

api_list.name: deleteSection
api_list.description: Note that sections must be empty to be deleted.

api_list.name: deleteTask
api_list.description: Deleted tasks go into the “trash” of the user making the delete request. Tasks can be recovered from the trash within a period of 30 days; afterward they are completely removed from the system.

api_list.name: deleteWebhook
api_list.description: This method permanently removes a webhook. Note that it may be possible to receive a request that was already in flight after deleting the webhook, but no further requests will be issued.

optional_parameters.name: sync

required_parameters.description: The project in which to search for tasks.

api_list.name: queryTypeahead
api_list.description: This method returns typeahead search results.

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: The type of object to look up. You can choose from one of the following: project, user, task, and tag. Note that unlike other endpoints, the types listed here are in singular form. Using multiple types is not yet supported.

required_parameters.name: query
required_parameters.description: The value to look up. This is a string that will be used to search for relevant objects. If an empty string is passed in, the API will currently return an empty set.

optional_parameters.name: count
optional_parameters.description: The number of results to return. The default is 20 if this parameter is omitted, with a minimum of 1 and a maximum of 100. If there are fewer results found than requested, all will be returned.

api_list.name: removeFollowersFromTask

api_list.name: removeTaskFromProject

api_list.name: reorderSections
api_list.description: At this point in time, moving sections is not supported in list views, only board views.

optional_parameters.name: beforeSection
optional_parameters.description: Insert the given section immediately before the section specified by this parameter.

optional_parameters.name: afterSection
optional_parameters.description: Insert the given section immediately before the section specified by this parameter.

api_list.name: typeaheadSearch
api_list.description: Retrieves objects in the workspace based on an auto-completion/typeahead search algorithm. This feature is meant to provide results quickly, so do not rely on this API to provide extremely accurate search results. The result set is limited to a single page of results with a maximum size, so you won’t be able to fetch large numbers of results.

required_parameters.name: workspace
required_parameters.description: The workspace to fetch objects from.

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: The type of values the typeahead should return. Note that unlike in the names of endpoints, the types listed here are in singular form (e.g. task). Using multiple types is not yet supported.

optional_parameters.name: query
optional_parameters.description: The string that will be used to search for relevant objects. If an empty string is passed in, the API will currently return an empty result set.

optional_parameters.name: count
optional_parameters.description: The number of results to return. The default is 20 if this parameter is omitted, with a minimum of 1 and a maximum of 100. If there are fewer results found than requested, all will be returned.

api_list.name: updateTag
